      "explanations": [
        "Certainly! To calculate the number of yards in 20 meters when 1 yard is equal to 0.9144 meters, you can use a similar approach as before. Let's break it down step by step:",
        "\\[ \\text{Number of yards in 20 meters} = \\frac{20}{0.9144} \\]",
        "Step 1: Set up the division:",
        "\\[ \\text{Number of yards in 20 meters} = \\frac{20}{0.9144} \\times \\frac{1}{1} \\]",
        "Step 2: Multiply the numerator and denominator by 1000 to clear the decimal from the divisor:",
        "\\[ \\text{Number of yards in 20 meters} = \\frac{20 \\times 1000}{0.9144 \\times 1000} \\]",
        "This simplifies to:",
        "\\[ \\text{Number of yards in 20 meters} = \\frac{20000}{914.4} \\]",
        "Step 3: Divide the numerator by the denominator:",
        "\\[ \\text{Number of yards in 20 meters} \\approx \\frac{20000}{914.4} \\]",
        "Now, perform the division:",
        "\\[ \\text{Number of yards in 20 meters} \\approx 21.8705 \\]",
        "So, there are approximately 21.8705 yards in 20 meters when 1 yard is equal to \\(0.9144\\) meters."
      ]
